00:00:52.990 --> 00:00:54.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:00:54.540 --> 00:00:55.767 align:middle line:90%
You are the one.

00:00:55.767 --> 00:00:57.100 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: No, you are the one.

00:00:57.100 --> 00:00:57.933 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No, you are.

00:00:57.933 --> 00:00:59.340 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: We are the one.

00:00:59.340 --> 00:01:00.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:01:00.410 --> 00:01:02.430 align:middle line:90%
You have an amazing background.

00:01:02.430 --> 00:01:03.960 align:middle line:90%
You grew up in West Africa.

00:01:03.960 --> 00:01:05.890 align:middle line:84%
What was your life like
when you were a boy?

00:01:05.890 --> 00:01:06.690 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: Yes.

00:01:06.690 --> 00:01:08.072 align:middle line:84%
I was born in
Ghana, West Africa.

00:01:08.072 --> 00:01:09.030 align:middle line:90%
My father's from Ghana.

00:01:09.030 --> 00:01:10.080 align:middle line:90%
Mother's Japanese.

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:12.870 align:middle line:90%
I pretty much grew up in London.

00:01:12.870 --> 00:01:14.790 align:middle line:84%
We had to leave Ghana
because of a coup.

00:01:14.790 --> 00:01:16.680 align:middle line:84%
My father was the
spiritual teacher

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:18.690 align:middle line:90%
to the president of Ghana.

00:01:18.690 --> 00:01:22.270 align:middle line:84%
And so my first memories as a
young boy was a deep calling.

00:01:22.270 --> 00:01:24.878 align:middle line:10%
I felt this deep
burning desire to make

00:01:24.878 --> 00:01:26.170 align:middle line:10%
a difference in people's lives.

00:01:26.170 --> 00:01:27.600 align:middle line:10%
I didn't know what it was
going to look like but I

00:01:27.600 --> 00:01:28.770 align:middle line:10%
felt this burning feeling.

00:01:28.770 --> 00:01:31.590 align:middle line:84%
And one of my first memories,
being a chubby kid in Ghana,

00:01:31.590 --> 00:01:33.210 align:middle line:84%
West Africa, I was
lost in the crowd

00:01:33.210 --> 00:01:36.240 align:middle line:84%
and I literally saw a crippled
woman crawling on the floor.

00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:39.150 align:middle line:84%
She picks up the sand this man
walks on, wipes it on her face

00:01:39.150 --> 00:01:40.050 align:middle line:90%
and stands up.

00:01:40.050 --> 00:01:42.510 align:middle line:84%
And so, week after week, I grew
up seeing blind people see,

00:01:42.510 --> 00:01:45.480 align:middle line:84%
and deaf people hear, and people
stand up out of wheelchairs.

00:01:45.480 --> 00:01:46.980 align:middle line:84%
The man whose sand
she picked up,

00:01:46.980 --> 00:01:49.440 align:middle line:84%
he would look at a woman in a
wheelchair and say, stand up.

00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:52.840 align:middle line:84%
The woman would say, but I
haven't walked in 20 years.

00:01:52.840 --> 00:01:53.640 align:middle line:90%
Stand up.

00:01:53.640 --> 00:01:54.728 align:middle line:90%
Do you believe?

00:01:54.728 --> 00:01:55.770 align:middle line:90%
If you believe, stand up.

00:01:55.770 --> 00:01:57.120 align:middle line:90%
And, boom, she would stand up.

00:01:57.120 --> 00:01:58.840 align:middle line:90%
So this man was my father.

00:01:58.840 --> 00:02:00.300 align:middle line:90%
He built 300 churches.

00:02:00.300 --> 00:02:03.330 align:middle line:84%
Even more, maybe a few
more, in Ghana, West Africa.

00:02:03.330 --> 00:02:05.700 align:middle line:10%
Huge church in London, UK.

00:02:05.700 --> 00:02:09.060 align:middle line:10%
And he probably had
300,000, 400,000 followers

00:02:09.060 --> 00:02:12.267 align:middle line:10%
in his congregation at the time.

00:02:12.267 --> 00:02:13.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You were the only child?

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:14.700 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: I was
the only child.

00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:15.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Watching all this.

00:02:15.750 --> 00:02:17.292 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: I saw
all this happening.

00:02:17.292 --> 00:02:18.330 align:middle line:90%
For me, it was normal.

00:02:18.330 --> 00:02:19.410 align:middle line:90%
Miracles were normal.

00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:22.660 align:middle line:84%
The supernatural
was just my reality.

00:02:22.660 --> 00:02:26.010 align:middle line:84%
I would go to school and I'd
tell my teachers and my friends

00:02:26.010 --> 00:02:27.780 align:middle line:84%
about the miracles
I saw on Sunday.

00:02:27.780 --> 00:02:28.710 align:middle line:90%
Nobody believed me.

00:02:28.710 --> 00:02:31.890 align:middle line:84%
One Sunday, my teacher
came to my father's church

00:02:31.890 --> 00:02:36.510 align:middle line:84%
and she saw this amazing thing
happening and had to apologize.

00:02:36.510 --> 00:02:38.880 align:middle line:84%
So it was a very unique
upbringing but very

00:02:38.880 --> 00:02:40.148 align:middle line:90%
normal for me at the time.

00:02:40.148 --> 00:02:42.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Normal is-- were you in
these congregations where you

00:02:42.690 --> 00:02:45.480 align:middle line:84%
would be a part of the prayer,
and the ceremony, and the--

00:02:45.480 --> 00:02:45.700 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: No.

00:02:45.700 --> 00:02:46.650 align:middle line:90%
I was the kid.

00:02:46.650 --> 00:02:49.080 align:middle line:84%
At eight years old, I just
wanted to play soccer.

00:02:49.080 --> 00:02:52.110 align:middle line:84%
Sunday service was five,
six hours on a Sunday,

00:02:52.110 --> 00:02:55.140 align:middle line:84%
clapping and singing and my
dad preaching for four hours.

00:02:55.140 --> 00:02:58.350 align:middle line:84%
And I was making
noise in this foyer

00:02:58.350 --> 00:03:01.290 align:middle line:84%
of the lobby of the church,
until one day my father

00:03:01.290 --> 00:03:04.015 align:middle line:84%
had someone drag me and
put me on the front row

00:03:04.015 --> 00:03:04.890 align:middle line:90%
and had me sit there.

00:03:04.890 --> 00:03:07.050 align:middle line:90%
I was falling asleep, age eight.

00:03:07.050 --> 00:03:08.940 align:middle line:84%
And that particular
Sunday, my father

00:03:08.940 --> 00:03:11.340 align:middle line:84%
says to the whole
congregation, my son

00:03:11.340 --> 00:03:14.110 align:middle line:84%
is going to give the sermon,
and they threw me onstage.

00:03:14.110 --> 00:03:17.813 align:middle line:84%
That's when my speaking
career began at age eight.

00:03:17.813 --> 00:03:18.730 align:middle line:90%
They threw me onstage.

00:03:18.730 --> 00:03:20.520 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea what
was happening.

00:03:20.520 --> 00:03:24.330 align:middle line:84%
And, literally, something
came through me.

00:03:24.330 --> 00:03:25.500 align:middle line:90%
Words came through me.

00:03:25.500 --> 00:03:28.170 align:middle line:84%
I just dissolved and
people started crying,

00:03:28.170 --> 00:03:31.330 align:middle line:84%
and that was the beginning of
the beginning of my speaking.

00:03:31.330 --> 00:03:33.300 align:middle line:84%
And that's really how
I feel when I speak.

00:03:33.300 --> 00:03:34.130 align:middle line:90%
I'm just not there.

00:03:34.130 --> 00:03:36.825 align:middle line:90%
I literally get out of the way.

00:03:36.825 --> 00:03:37.950 align:middle line:90%
And that's what started it.

00:03:37.950 --> 00:03:39.900 align:middle line:84%
But when I was
14, my father also

00:03:39.900 --> 00:03:42.090 align:middle line:84%
announced to the
congregation, my son

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:44.082 align:middle line:90%
is taking over my ministry.

00:03:44.082 --> 00:03:45.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did he
consult you on this?

00:03:45.540 --> 00:03:47.460 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: No
conversation whatsoever.

00:03:47.460 --> 00:03:51.000 align:middle line:84%
My father and I, we
weren't so close.

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:54.180 align:middle line:84%
He was out there serving
the world, so I loved him.

00:03:54.180 --> 00:03:56.310 align:middle line:84%
But when he announced
to the congregation,

00:03:56.310 --> 00:04:00.330 align:middle line:84%
my son is taking
over, my heart sunk.

00:04:00.330 --> 00:04:02.610 align:middle line:84%
Because as much as I wanted
to make a difference,

00:04:02.610 --> 00:04:04.410 align:middle line:84%
as much as I wanted
to serve people--

00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:06.510 align:middle line:90%
and this is all I knew--

00:04:06.510 --> 00:04:11.220 align:middle line:84%
deep down, I knew in my heart
that this was not my path.

00:04:11.220 --> 00:04:13.810 align:middle line:90%
I felt something wasn't aligned.

00:04:13.810 --> 00:04:15.727 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't know
what else to do.

00:04:15.727 --> 00:04:17.310 align:middle line:84%
From a young age,
age eight, I started

00:04:17.310 --> 00:04:21.540 align:middle line:84%
reading literally hundreds of
books in terms of psychology,

00:04:21.540 --> 00:04:23.130 align:middle line:90%
spirituality, meditation.

00:04:23.130 --> 00:04:26.095 align:middle line:84%
My first book was by a woman
called Shakti Gawain, "Creative

00:04:26.095 --> 00:04:26.895 align:middle line:90%
Visualization."

00:04:26.895 --> 00:04:27.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mine too.

00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:28.340 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: Age eight, right?

00:04:28.340 --> 00:04:28.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mine too.

00:04:28.780 --> 00:04:29.863 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: She was like--

00:04:29.863 --> 00:04:31.140 align:middle line:90%
give me five.

00:04:31.140 --> 00:04:33.550 align:middle line:90%
She was like the original.

00:04:33.550 --> 00:04:35.670 align:middle line:84%
Think-- if you can
believe it and see it,

00:04:35.670 --> 00:04:36.720 align:middle line:90%
then you can achieve it.

00:04:36.720 --> 00:04:39.540 align:middle line:84%
And so this is how I started,
reading Shakti Gawain, Ernest

00:04:39.540 --> 00:04:42.960 align:middle line:84%
Holmes, Unity, Charles Filmore,
people like Johnnie Colemon.

00:04:42.960 --> 00:04:46.125 align:middle line:84%
Old school metaphysicians,
Joseph Murphy, Neville Goddard.

00:04:46.125 --> 00:04:49.400 align:middle line:84%
To the Western, Wayne Dyer,
Louise Hay, Deepak Chopra.

00:04:49.400 --> 00:04:53.250 align:middle line:84%
So, for me, spirituality,
personal growth was my passion,

00:04:53.250 --> 00:04:56.448 align:middle line:84%
and asking myself the questions
who am I, and why am I here,

00:04:56.448 --> 00:04:57.740 align:middle line:90%
and what's the purpose of life.

00:04:57.740 --> 00:05:01.350 align:middle line:84%
And I look at life and
I knew it wasn't right.

00:05:01.350 --> 00:05:04.500 align:middle line:84%
There's some things-- we all
have an experience-- maybe it's

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:06.570 align:middle line:84%
a relationship we're
in, maybe it's a job,

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:08.550 align:middle line:84%
maybe it's a business
dealing-- where

00:05:08.550 --> 00:05:12.510 align:middle line:90%
we know something isn't right.

00:05:12.510 --> 00:05:14.640 align:middle line:84%
Everything logically wants
to go in that direction

00:05:14.640 --> 00:05:16.320 align:middle line:90%
but something isn't aligned.

00:05:16.320 --> 00:05:17.730 align:middle line:90%
I knew it wasn't aligned.

00:05:17.730 --> 00:05:20.310 align:middle line:84%
But the truth is
I wanted his love.

00:05:20.310 --> 00:05:23.310 align:middle line:84%
I was afraid that if
I honored my truth,

00:05:23.310 --> 00:05:25.230 align:middle line:84%
I was afraid if
I spoke my truth,

00:05:25.230 --> 00:05:28.900 align:middle line:84%
I was afraid if I dared to be
who I really was and tell him,

00:05:28.900 --> 00:05:31.770 align:middle line:84%
Dad, I don't think this
is my path in life,

00:05:31.770 --> 00:05:34.800 align:middle line:84%
that I would lose his love, I
would lose the relationship,

00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:36.960 align:middle line:84%
I would be outcast,
I'd be alone,

00:05:36.960 --> 00:05:38.910 align:middle line:84%
I'd lose the connection
to the community.

00:05:38.910 --> 00:05:42.510 align:middle line:84%
So I literally,
somewhat consciously,

00:05:42.510 --> 00:05:45.270 align:middle line:84%
suppressed my truth
deep inside for years.

00:05:45.270 --> 00:05:49.980 align:middle line:84%
It took me four years of
suffering and internal turmoil.

00:05:49.980 --> 00:05:52.830 align:middle line:84%
Because we know when
something isn't aligned.

00:05:52.830 --> 00:05:55.560 align:middle line:84%
And I think when we
dishonor ourselves,

00:05:55.560 --> 00:05:57.510 align:middle line:84%
there is no greater
betrayal, there

00:05:57.510 --> 00:06:02.550 align:middle line:84%
is no greater pain that arises
from not honoring our truth.

00:06:02.550 --> 00:06:04.320 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I was going
to leave school

00:06:04.320 --> 00:06:07.542 align:middle line:84%
when I was 16 because I figured
life has more to teach me.

00:06:07.542 --> 00:06:09.750 align:middle line:84%
And so I chose not to go to
university, which already

00:06:09.750 --> 00:06:11.995 align:middle line:90%
was a very abnormal decision.

00:06:11.995 --> 00:06:16.590 align:middle line:84%
It went against the culture
and the collective desire

00:06:16.590 --> 00:06:18.520 align:middle line:90%
of my community.

00:06:18.520 --> 00:06:19.980 align:middle line:84%
But I looked into
my future, Lisa,

00:06:19.980 --> 00:06:24.870 align:middle line:84%
and I literally saw I could
take the expected path.

00:06:24.870 --> 00:06:27.930 align:middle line:84%
I could follow my father's
vision for my life.

00:06:27.930 --> 00:06:29.310 align:middle line:84%
And I literally
felt the pressure

00:06:29.310 --> 00:06:32.440 align:middle line:84%
of hundreds of thousands of
people, the expectations.

00:06:32.440 --> 00:06:35.490 align:middle line:84%
And I realized there's no
shortage of people in life

00:06:35.490 --> 00:06:38.340 align:middle line:84%
that will think they know
what your life should be,

00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:40.440 align:middle line:84%
that they think they
know who you should be

00:06:40.440 --> 00:06:43.170 align:middle line:84%
and how you should live, and
it takes a tremendous amount

00:06:43.170 --> 00:06:46.590 align:middle line:84%
of courage to follow your
truth, to follow your knowing,

00:06:46.590 --> 00:06:49.592 align:middle line:84%
when everyone around
you is pressuring you

00:06:49.592 --> 00:06:50.550 align:middle line:90%
in a certain direction.

00:06:50.550 --> 00:06:51.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You didn't
just have him.

00:06:51.420 --> 00:06:51.630 align:middle line:90%
You had--

00:06:51.630 --> 00:06:53.400 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: I had
the expectations.

00:06:53.400 --> 00:06:54.930 align:middle line:90%
I was the guy.

00:06:54.930 --> 00:06:56.610 align:middle line:84%
And so I looked
into my future and I

00:06:56.610 --> 00:07:01.470 align:middle line:84%
saw myself at 28, and
38, and 48, and 50.

00:07:01.470 --> 00:07:03.430 align:middle line:84%
And I looked at the
trajectory of my life

00:07:03.430 --> 00:07:06.820 align:middle line:84%
and I saw I might be successful
by everyone else's standards,

00:07:06.820 --> 00:07:09.795 align:middle line:84%
but if I didn't have
myself, then I had nothing.

00:07:09.795 --> 00:07:11.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Your realized
that 18 years old.

00:07:11.910 --> 00:07:14.160 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: I felt
the pain of that.

00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:18.060 align:middle line:84%
Then I looked into the unknown
and everything felt deeply

00:07:18.060 --> 00:07:22.590 align:middle line:84%
authentically right, but it
was just like a black void of I

00:07:22.590 --> 00:07:25.230 align:middle line:84%
have no idea what I'm
doing, where I'm going.

00:07:25.230 --> 00:07:28.890 align:middle line:90%
But inside, it felt right.

00:07:28.890 --> 00:07:31.670 align:middle line:84%
So I had to make peace
with I have no idea.

00:07:31.670 --> 00:07:33.700 align:middle line:84%
I had to make peace
with the unknown,

00:07:33.700 --> 00:07:36.150 align:middle line:84%
and I chose to have a
conversation with my father.

00:07:36.150 --> 00:07:40.170 align:middle line:84%
One day, I literally
went into his bedroom.

00:07:40.170 --> 00:07:42.780 align:middle line:84%
Basically, I had
to first make peace

00:07:42.780 --> 00:07:45.060 align:middle line:84%
with letting go of my
relationship with him.

00:07:45.060 --> 00:07:45.900 align:middle line:90%
I had to decide.

00:07:45.900 --> 00:07:48.273 align:middle line:84%
Like I may never have
a relationship with him

00:07:48.273 --> 00:07:49.690 align:middle line:84%
and I had to make
peace with that.

00:07:49.690 --> 00:07:50.523 align:middle line:90%
That was number one.

00:07:50.523 --> 00:07:52.380 align:middle line:84%
And I finally had the
conversation with him.

00:07:52.380 --> 00:07:55.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that moment
must have been--

00:07:55.110 --> 00:07:57.970 align:middle line:84%
you write about it in your book,
where you said to your mother,

00:07:57.970 --> 00:07:59.190 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go up
those stairs and I'm

00:07:59.190 --> 00:08:00.315 align:middle line:90%
going to talk to my father.

00:08:00.315 --> 00:08:01.770 align:middle line:90%
What was that like for you?

00:08:01.770 --> 00:08:03.060 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: Terrifying.

00:08:03.060 --> 00:08:07.890 align:middle line:84%
I knew what I had to do
in my heart, in my soul.

00:08:07.890 --> 00:08:10.710 align:middle line:84%
There was no question
my soul was pulling me.

00:08:10.710 --> 00:08:12.990 align:middle line:84%
But the day I
decided, I remember

00:08:12.990 --> 00:08:16.950 align:middle line:84%
I walked up the stairs of my
tiny apartment where we lived.

00:08:16.950 --> 00:08:20.370 align:middle line:84%
My father was lying on
the bed, just sleeping.

00:08:20.370 --> 00:08:21.750 align:middle line:90%
I tapped him on the shoulder.

00:08:21.750 --> 00:08:22.900 align:middle line:90%
My mother was behind me.

00:08:22.900 --> 00:08:24.490 align:middle line:90%
I felt her support.

00:08:24.490 --> 00:08:27.700 align:middle line:84%
This was the moment my entire
life was about to shift

00:08:27.700 --> 00:08:28.500 align:middle line:90%
and shifted.

00:08:28.500 --> 00:08:30.480 align:middle line:84%
And I tapped him
on the shoulder.

00:08:30.480 --> 00:08:33.360 align:middle line:84%
I said, Dad, I have
something to tell you.

00:08:33.360 --> 00:08:34.500 align:middle line:90%
He said, what, my son?

00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:36.750 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I don't
feel I'm meant

00:08:36.750 --> 00:08:38.440 align:middle line:90%
to take over your churches.

00:08:38.440 --> 00:08:39.960 align:middle line:90%
I kind of mumbled it.

00:08:39.960 --> 00:08:41.789 align:middle line:90%
And then he said, are you sure?

00:08:41.789 --> 00:08:44.480 align:middle line:90%
I said, yes.

00:08:44.480 --> 00:08:45.840 align:middle line:90%
He said, are you sure?

00:08:45.840 --> 00:08:47.700 align:middle line:90%
I said, yes.

00:08:47.700 --> 00:08:49.830 align:middle line:90%
He said, OK.

00:08:49.830 --> 00:08:51.280 align:middle line:90%
And that was it.

00:08:51.280 --> 00:08:52.970 align:middle line:84%
I thought he was
going to scream.

00:08:52.970 --> 00:08:53.910 align:middle line:90%
It was worse.

00:08:53.910 --> 00:08:57.067 align:middle line:84%
And it was the scariest,
at least until that moment,

00:08:57.067 --> 00:08:58.650 align:middle line:84%
it was the scariest
moment of my life,

00:08:58.650 --> 00:09:00.108 align:middle line:84%
because I thought
I'm about to lose

00:09:00.108 --> 00:09:01.950 align:middle line:90%
my relationship with my father.

00:09:01.950 --> 00:09:05.170 align:middle line:90%
We didn't speak for two years.

00:09:05.170 --> 00:09:05.970 align:middle line:90%
It was terrifying.

00:09:05.970 --> 00:09:07.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Did you feel relief.

00:09:07.260 --> 00:09:08.610 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: I felt relief.

00:09:08.610 --> 00:09:11.700 align:middle line:90%
I felt nervous.

00:09:11.700 --> 00:09:12.930 align:middle line:90%
I felt excited.

00:09:12.930 --> 00:09:15.390 align:middle line:84%
I knew it was the
right decision.

00:09:15.390 --> 00:09:17.190 align:middle line:84%
But there was also
a lot of pain,

00:09:17.190 --> 00:09:22.350 align:middle line:84%
because I knew I felt like I
was letting my father down.

00:09:22.350 --> 00:09:24.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What did you
do right after that?

00:09:24.100 --> 00:09:25.960 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's not like
you could go back to--

00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:32.280 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: I sat in my room and
stared at the wall in silence.

00:09:32.280 --> 00:09:35.190 align:middle line:84%
And I knew there
was no turning back.

00:09:35.190 --> 00:09:39.480 align:middle line:84%
Because even if I told my
father, oh, that was a mistake,

00:09:39.480 --> 00:09:42.010 align:middle line:90%
the bond is cut at that moment.

00:09:42.010 --> 00:09:45.090 align:middle line:84%
And so it was a huge
destiny choice point.

00:09:45.090 --> 00:09:48.450 align:middle line:84%
And I think in life we
have moments of choices

00:09:48.450 --> 00:09:49.590 align:middle line:90%
that our soul has.

00:09:49.590 --> 00:09:51.285 align:middle line:90%
And I think we have to be--

00:09:51.285 --> 00:09:53.160 align:middle line:84%
sometimes we think we
have to get rid of fear

00:09:53.160 --> 00:09:55.090 align:middle line:84%
and have no fear in
order to move forward.

00:09:55.090 --> 00:09:56.340 align:middle line:90%
I believe that, no.

00:09:56.340 --> 00:09:57.840 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes you will
feel the fear,

00:09:57.840 --> 00:09:59.730 align:middle line:84%
and the way through the
fear is through the fear,

00:09:59.730 --> 00:10:01.647 align:middle line:84%
is to feel the fear and
step through the fear.

00:10:01.647 --> 00:10:04.620 align:middle line:84%
And by stepping through the
fear and having the courage,

00:10:04.620 --> 00:10:06.730 align:middle line:90%
that you expand your capacity.

00:10:06.730 --> 00:10:08.730 align:middle line:84%
And that's kind of how I
see people like Gandhi.

00:10:08.730 --> 00:10:11.010 align:middle line:84%
They probably felt fear but
they kept stepping through.

00:10:11.010 --> 00:10:11.870 align:middle line:90%
And then they expanded.

00:10:11.870 --> 00:10:13.870 align:middle line:84%
They kept stepping through,
they kept expanding.

00:10:13.870 --> 00:10:16.842 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
that's when greatness

00:10:16.842 --> 00:10:19.300 align:middle line:84%
is a moment-to-moment choice,
and that was a choice for me.

00:10:19.300 --> 00:10:20.383 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is beautiful.

00:10:20.383 --> 00:10:23.290 align:middle line:84%
Because most people run away
from fear and confrontation

00:10:23.290 --> 00:10:25.540 align:middle line:84%
and that moment, and I
don't want to have that.

00:10:25.540 --> 00:10:31.090 align:middle line:84%
And you just go into it and
into it and make it alive,

00:10:31.090 --> 00:10:32.660 align:middle line:90%
and you confronted it right on.

00:10:32.660 --> 00:10:34.950 align:middle line:84%
And it started at an
early age for you.

00:10:34.950 --> 00:10:36.970 align:middle line:90%
That's a huge lesson.

00:10:36.970 --> 00:10:37.940 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: Yes.

00:10:37.940 --> 00:10:42.620 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that I think
keeps us stuck and unhappy

00:10:42.620 --> 00:10:46.630 align:middle line:84%
are literally all the ways
that we lie to ourselves, all

00:10:46.630 --> 00:10:48.610 align:middle line:90%
the ways that we BS ourselves.

00:10:48.610 --> 00:10:50.970 align:middle line:84%
We rationalize, we
don't tell the truth.

00:10:50.970 --> 00:10:53.960 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I'm in a
relationship and it's OK.

00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:54.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: We cope.

00:10:54.760 --> 00:10:55.593 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: We cope.

00:10:55.593 --> 00:10:57.910 align:middle line:84%
We make it OK,
when, deep down, we

00:10:57.910 --> 00:11:01.570 align:middle line:84%
know this relationship
is no longer aligned

00:11:01.570 --> 00:11:02.650 align:middle line:90%
with who I am today.

00:11:02.650 --> 00:11:04.720 align:middle line:84%
This relationship is
no longer honoring me.

00:11:04.720 --> 00:11:07.120 align:middle line:84%
But maybe we've invested
so much time in this--

00:11:07.120 --> 00:11:11.110 align:middle line:84%
10 years, 20 years, 30 years--
that what will people say?

00:11:11.110 --> 00:11:13.870 align:middle line:84%
So maybe there's that fear,
of letting go of the known,

00:11:13.870 --> 00:11:15.250 align:middle line:84%
letting go of
what's comfortable.

00:11:15.250 --> 00:11:18.700 align:middle line:84%
Maybe we work a job and
we know it's not right.

00:11:18.700 --> 00:11:20.710 align:middle line:84%
We know it doesn't
give us the opportunity

00:11:20.710 --> 00:11:24.040 align:middle line:84%
to express our gifts, our
heart, our true purpose.

00:11:24.040 --> 00:11:25.723 align:middle line:84%
But we stay because
we're afraid how

00:11:25.723 --> 00:11:26.890 align:middle line:90%
am I going to pay the bills?

00:11:26.890 --> 00:11:28.710 align:middle line:90%
How am I going to survive?

00:11:28.710 --> 00:11:29.833 align:middle line:90%
So, for me--

00:11:29.833 --> 00:11:31.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Fear keeps us stuck.

00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:32.333 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: Fear keeps us stuck.

00:11:32.333 --> 00:11:36.100 align:middle line:84%
And so I think we have to
be willing, as a first step,

00:11:36.100 --> 00:11:38.360 align:middle line:90%
to tell the truth to ourselves.

00:11:38.360 --> 00:11:39.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Selves.

00:11:39.160 --> 00:11:39.960 align:middle line:90%
Ourselves first.

00:11:39.960 --> 00:11:42.130 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: That is
like key number one.

00:11:42.130 --> 00:11:44.000 align:middle line:90%
I say happiness is easy.

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:44.950 align:middle line:90%
It's actually-- no.

00:11:44.950 --> 00:11:47.760 align:middle line:84%
Happiness is simple,
not always easy.

00:11:47.760 --> 00:11:52.180 align:middle line:84%
Feel the truth, own the
truth, acknowledge the truth,

00:11:52.180 --> 00:11:54.160 align:middle line:90%
tell the truth, live the truth.

00:11:54.160 --> 00:11:55.270 align:middle line:90%
Happy life.

00:11:55.270 --> 00:11:57.435 align:middle line:84%
But not always easy
because of human fear.

00:11:57.435 --> 00:11:58.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You hear
people say that.

00:11:58.810 --> 00:12:00.610 align:middle line:84%
They say, oh, I've
got the best life.

00:12:00.610 --> 00:12:03.550 align:middle line:84%
You wouldn't understand why I'm
so deeply unhappy, because it

00:12:03.550 --> 00:12:05.200 align:middle line:90%
looks great from the outside.

00:12:05.200 --> 00:12:07.720 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: Sometimes people
think, oh, you follow your path

00:12:07.720 --> 00:12:11.030 align:middle line:84%
and the unicorns come
out and it's easy.

00:12:11.030 --> 00:12:13.280 align:middle line:84%
And everything is the
spontaneous fulfillment

00:12:13.280 --> 00:12:14.080 align:middle line:90%
of your desire.

00:12:14.080 --> 00:12:14.530 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:12:14.530 --> 00:12:17.110 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, when you follow
your path and your purpose,

00:12:17.110 --> 00:12:18.850 align:middle line:90%
you will face challenges.

00:12:18.850 --> 00:12:22.210 align:middle line:84%
Those challenges are simply
the preparation for your soul

00:12:22.210 --> 00:12:25.060 align:middle line:84%
to develop the soul
muscle, the soul force,

00:12:25.060 --> 00:12:28.830 align:middle line:84%
to be able to face
the challenges

00:12:28.830 --> 00:12:31.082 align:middle line:84%
and what it's
going to take to be

00:12:31.082 --> 00:12:32.290 align:middle line:90%
able to fulfill your purpose.

00:12:32.290 --> 00:12:33.800 align:middle line:84%
So we didn't speak
for two years.

00:12:33.800 --> 00:12:35.180 align:middle line:90%
It was very difficult.

00:12:35.180 --> 00:12:37.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: During those two
years, what did you do?

00:12:37.180 --> 00:12:39.520 align:middle line:90%
You came to California, right?

00:12:39.520 --> 00:12:41.380 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: So we didn't speak.

00:12:41.380 --> 00:12:43.750 align:middle line:84%
And then I thought,
oh my goodness.

00:12:43.750 --> 00:12:45.340 align:middle line:90%
God, what am I going to do?

00:12:45.340 --> 00:12:49.410 align:middle line:84%
My feeling was, universe,
you've given me this vision.

00:12:49.410 --> 00:12:50.660 align:middle line:90%
Because I felt a vision, Lisa.

00:12:50.660 --> 00:12:51.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You had the faith.

00:12:51.520 --> 00:12:52.687 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: I had the faith.

00:12:52.687 --> 00:12:53.860 align:middle line:90%
I had a calling.

00:12:53.860 --> 00:12:54.910 align:middle line:90%
I felt this purpose.

00:12:54.910 --> 00:12:57.280 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I had
to come to the US.

00:12:57.280 --> 00:12:59.063 align:middle line:84%
I had to come to Los
Angeles because this

00:12:59.063 --> 00:13:00.730 align:middle line:84%
is where all the
authors who wrote books

00:13:00.730 --> 00:13:04.188 align:middle line:84%
were living, the Tony Robbins,
the Louise Hays, the Chopras,

00:13:04.188 --> 00:13:05.230 align:middle line:90%
the Marianne Williamsons.

00:13:05.230 --> 00:13:07.040 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to come and
find these people.

00:13:07.040 --> 00:13:08.590 align:middle line:90%
And so one day I said a prayer.

00:13:08.590 --> 00:13:11.980 align:middle line:84%
I said, universe, God,
you've given me this vision.

00:13:11.980 --> 00:13:14.800 align:middle line:84%
If this is true, if
this vision is true,

00:13:14.800 --> 00:13:16.020 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what to do.

00:13:16.020 --> 00:13:16.820 align:middle line:90%
I have no support.

00:13:16.820 --> 00:13:17.660 align:middle line:90%
I have no money.

00:13:17.660 --> 00:13:18.460 align:middle line:90%
Help me.

00:13:18.460 --> 00:13:19.390 align:middle line:90%
Help me.

00:13:19.390 --> 00:13:21.460 align:middle line:90%
Literally within 24 hours--

00:13:21.460 --> 00:13:22.750 align:middle line:90%
I was in the library--

00:13:22.750 --> 00:13:25.420 align:middle line:84%
someone hands me a magazine
called "The Economist."

00:13:25.420 --> 00:13:26.590 align:middle line:90%
I feel chills.

00:13:26.590 --> 00:13:28.060 align:middle line:84%
We always have to
follow the clues.

00:13:28.060 --> 00:13:28.942 align:middle line:90%
I feel these chills.

00:13:28.942 --> 00:13:30.400 align:middle line:84%
I look in the back
of the magazine.

00:13:30.400 --> 00:13:32.317 align:middle line:84%
It says the American
government is giving away

00:13:32.317 --> 00:13:36.310 align:middle line:84%
55,000 green cards in
the green card lottery.

00:13:36.310 --> 00:13:39.090 align:middle line:84%
Everything in my soul
said, you're going to win.

00:13:39.090 --> 00:13:40.070 align:middle line:90%
Enter it.

00:13:40.070 --> 00:13:42.573 align:middle line:84%
But many times, we feel this
intuition but we don't follow.

00:13:42.573 --> 00:13:43.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Always say
there's no way.

00:13:43.990 --> 00:13:44.530 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: There's no way.

00:13:44.530 --> 00:13:45.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a hoax.

00:13:45.640 --> 00:13:47.320 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: Our mind
gets in the way.

00:13:47.320 --> 00:13:48.380 align:middle line:90%
You know, I was naive.

00:13:48.380 --> 00:13:48.880 align:middle line:90%
I was 18.

00:13:48.880 --> 00:13:49.810 align:middle line:90%
I entered it.

00:13:49.810 --> 00:13:52.040 align:middle line:84%
Cut a long story short,
three months later

00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:53.830 align:middle line:90%
I was told I won a green card.

00:13:53.830 --> 00:13:56.440 align:middle line:84%
I literally won a green
card in a lottery.

00:13:56.440 --> 00:14:00.250 align:middle line:84%
And that, for me, was the
sign from the universe

00:14:00.250 --> 00:14:01.870 align:middle line:90%
that I was being guided.

00:14:01.870 --> 00:14:04.270 align:middle line:84%
The day I found out,
I was so shocked,

00:14:04.270 --> 00:14:06.440 align:middle line:90%
and celebrating, and excited.

00:14:06.440 --> 00:14:08.275 align:middle line:90%
And I heard a voice say--

00:14:08.275 --> 00:14:10.330 align:middle line:90%
it's in a voice--

00:14:10.330 --> 00:14:12.250 align:middle line:90%
why do you seem so surprised?

00:14:12.250 --> 00:14:13.330 align:middle line:90%
Did you not know?

00:14:13.330 --> 00:14:14.260 align:middle line:90%
You knew.

00:14:14.260 --> 00:14:16.060 align:middle line:90%
Trust your knowing.

00:14:16.060 --> 00:14:18.550 align:middle line:84%
That was a moment where
I knew I was being

00:14:18.550 --> 00:14:19.952 align:middle line:90%
guided throughout my life.

00:14:19.952 --> 00:14:21.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But it took a
while for that green card

00:14:21.910 --> 00:14:22.868 align:middle line:90%
to come through, right?

00:14:22.868 --> 00:14:25.180 align:middle line:84%
Didn't you doubt when
it didn't come through?

00:14:25.180 --> 00:14:28.240 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: Every day I
would run to the mailbox.

00:14:28.240 --> 00:14:31.630 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I literally
drew on a piece of paper

00:14:31.630 --> 00:14:35.630 align:middle line:84%
a card colored green and
put my face and name on it.

00:14:35.630 --> 00:14:36.490 align:middle line:90%
I was visual--

00:14:36.490 --> 00:14:39.190 align:middle line:84%
I read Shakti Gawain's
"Creative Visualization."

00:14:39.190 --> 00:14:41.380 align:middle line:84%
I was visualizing
myself in America.

00:14:41.380 --> 00:14:44.020 align:middle line:84%
I was visualizing the
president of the US--

00:14:44.020 --> 00:14:45.770 align:middle line:90%
I think Clinton at the time--

00:14:45.770 --> 00:14:46.570 align:middle line:90%
welcoming.

00:14:46.570 --> 00:14:48.882 align:middle line:84%
I didn't realize I wasn't
going to get a welcome.

00:14:48.882 --> 00:14:50.590 align:middle line:84%
So I was visualizing
all of these things.

00:14:50.590 --> 00:14:51.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You know
that window shut

00:14:51.430 --> 00:14:52.555 align:middle line:90%
after that happened to you.

00:14:52.555 --> 00:14:55.540 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: And every
day, no confirmation

00:14:55.540 --> 00:14:57.520 align:middle line:90%
until the very final day.

00:14:57.520 --> 00:14:59.680 align:middle line:84%
The very final day is
when I got a phone call

00:14:59.680 --> 00:15:01.745 align:middle line:84%
from the lawyer I applied
through, that said,

00:15:01.745 --> 00:15:02.620 align:middle line:90%
you won a green card.

00:15:02.620 --> 00:15:04.670 align:middle line:90%
And that gave me a knowing.

00:15:04.670 --> 00:15:07.300 align:middle line:84%
So I realize any time
I've doubted, any time

00:15:07.300 --> 00:15:10.425 align:middle line:84%
even since then, when I've lost
faith or question-- because I

00:15:10.425 --> 00:15:12.550 align:middle line:84%
think we all question, is
my dream going to happen?

00:15:12.550 --> 00:15:13.910 align:middle line:90%
Is my soulmate going to happen?

00:15:13.910 --> 00:15:14.920 align:middle line:90%
Is it going to happen for me?

00:15:14.920 --> 00:15:16.840 align:middle line:84%
I see it happening for
all these other people.

00:15:16.840 --> 00:15:19.370 align:middle line:84%
I go back to that
moment and I remember.

00:15:19.370 --> 00:15:22.710 align:middle line:84%
You didn't come this far to
be left where you are now.

00:15:22.710 --> 00:15:25.297 align:middle line:84%
And so that moment
gives me a lot of faith.

00:15:25.297 --> 00:15:27.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you didn't
lose your faith in between.

00:15:27.380 --> 00:15:29.030 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot to
learn from that.

00:15:29.030 --> 00:15:31.070 align:middle line:84%
Because things don't
happen in the time

00:15:31.070 --> 00:15:34.130 align:middle line:84%
that we order them to happen,
when we want them to happen.

00:15:34.130 --> 00:15:37.050 align:middle line:84%
And your faith was
probably tested many times.

00:15:37.050 --> 00:15:37.850 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: Many.

00:15:37.850 --> 00:15:41.270 align:middle line:84%
Like many times over the last 20
some years I've been in the US,

00:15:41.270 --> 00:15:45.310 align:middle line:84%
my faith has been
tested over and over.

00:15:45.310 --> 00:15:47.810 align:middle line:84%
It's not it's not like you read
a book or you write a book--

00:15:47.810 --> 00:15:48.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's great to hear.

00:15:48.970 --> 00:15:50.095 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: --and it stops.

00:15:50.095 --> 00:15:53.150 align:middle line:84%
But what I realized is
sometimes when your dreams

00:15:53.150 --> 00:15:56.180 align:middle line:84%
don't manifest--
because it does happen--

00:15:56.180 --> 00:16:01.190 align:middle line:84%
we get depressed, we
lose faith, we give up.

00:16:01.190 --> 00:16:03.455 align:middle line:84%
For me, there's a few
things that it means when

00:16:03.455 --> 00:16:04.580 align:middle line:90%
your dreams don't manifest.

00:16:04.580 --> 00:16:08.360 align:middle line:84%
The first thing I would say is
it might mean that your dream

00:16:08.360 --> 00:16:10.730 align:middle line:84%
or what you think is
your goal, vision,

00:16:10.730 --> 00:16:13.460 align:middle line:84%
and dream is
actually not aligned

00:16:13.460 --> 00:16:15.390 align:middle line:90%
with your highest purpose.

00:16:15.390 --> 00:16:18.140 align:middle line:84%
It's just you think you want
that car, or that house,

00:16:18.140 --> 00:16:21.590 align:middle line:84%
or that project, or to
be that actor or actress,

00:16:21.590 --> 00:16:24.920 align:middle line:84%
but it's not really the
most authentic expression

00:16:24.920 --> 00:16:27.930 align:middle line:84%
of what you are here
to do in your lifetime.

00:16:27.930 --> 00:16:29.480 align:middle line:84%
And so when you
push and you push

00:16:29.480 --> 00:16:31.880 align:middle line:84%
and you push for that TV
show and it doesn't happen,

00:16:31.880 --> 00:16:33.508 align:middle line:84%
or that project,
it doesn't happen,

00:16:33.508 --> 00:16:34.800 align:middle line:90%
doesn't mean something's wrong.

00:16:34.800 --> 00:16:36.830 align:middle line:84%
It just means you have
to maybe dig deeper,

00:16:36.830 --> 00:16:39.650 align:middle line:90%
feel deeper, feel into what is--

00:16:39.650 --> 00:16:41.120 align:middle line:90%
maybe there's something more.

00:16:41.120 --> 00:16:44.750 align:middle line:84%
Maybe there's something else
that you're really meant to do,

00:16:44.750 --> 00:16:47.070 align:middle line:84%
so we have to be willing
to surrender and let go.

00:16:47.070 --> 00:16:50.450 align:middle line:84%
The other thing is
sometimes it's just timing.

00:16:50.450 --> 00:16:52.190 align:middle line:84%
I mean, in my life,
for the longest time,

00:16:52.190 --> 00:16:53.090 align:middle line:90%
I wanted the book to happen.

00:16:53.090 --> 00:16:55.250 align:middle line:84%
For the longest time, I
wanted TV projects to happen.

00:16:55.250 --> 00:16:56.210 align:middle line:90%
They weren't happening.

00:16:56.210 --> 00:17:01.400 align:middle line:84%
But I realize now sometimes
things not happening is grace,

00:17:01.400 --> 00:17:03.950 align:middle line:84%
is the biggest blessing
from the universe.

00:17:03.950 --> 00:17:05.780 align:middle line:84%
Because had they
happened in the time

00:17:05.780 --> 00:17:08.690 align:middle line:84%
that I wanted them to
happen, I wasn't ready yet

00:17:08.690 --> 00:17:10.890 align:middle line:84%
and it would have
probably been a disaster.

00:17:10.890 --> 00:17:12.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I remember one
of the first music videos

00:17:12.890 --> 00:17:18.950 align:middle line:84%
that you did, and it had
almost a quarter million views.

00:17:18.950 --> 00:17:22.460 align:middle line:90%
And this was like 2004?

00:17:22.460 --> 00:17:23.490 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: 2009.

00:17:23.490 --> 00:17:24.410 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Nine.

00:17:24.410 --> 00:17:24.800 align:middle line:90%
Nine.

00:17:24.800 --> 00:17:25.819 align:middle line:90%
When you came--

00:17:25.819 --> 00:17:26.420 align:middle line:90%
>>BLACKSON: First year.

00:17:26.420 --> 00:17:27.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:27.220 --> 00:17:30.480 align:middle line:84%
And it was really too-- we have
a clip here I want you to see.

00:17:30.480 --> 00:17:31.280 align:middle line:90%
Just take a look.

00:17:31.280 --> 00:17:33.230 align:middle line:84%
It's really truly
feeling into you.

00:17:33.230 --> 00:17:42.170 align:middle line:90%


00:17:42.170 --> 00:17:44.120 align:middle line:84%
>>BLACKSON: When you
were first conceived,

00:17:44.120 --> 00:17:48.740 align:middle line:84%
you were a double strand of
DNA in a fertilized ovum.

00:17:48.740 --> 00:17:55.070 align:middle line:10%
